traceability.evidence:
In src/print-outdated.js the age filtering only checks the age of info.latest and filters out packages younger than the threshold; it never iterates over earlier versions (REQ-SMART-SEARCH) to find the newest mature version. Additionally, there is no logic to skip packages where the mature version is <= current version (REQ-COMPARISON), e.g.:

  // Filter by age threshold (using appropriate threshold per dependency type)
  const matureRows = rows.filter(([_name, , , , age, depType]) => {
    const minAge = depType === 'prod' ? prodMinAge : devMinAge;
    return typeof age === 'number' && age >= minAge;
  });

No subsequent check excludes rows with latest <= current. These missing behaviors violate the “Smart Filtering” and “Skip Current” acceptance criteria.
